<item>
 <title>Helpful Hints for Living on the Stipend </title>
 <link>http://digitalartscorps.org/node/1749</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This list was brainstormed by DASCorps members during the 2010 PSO. &lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Health and Wellness&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•   Get a bike&lt;br /&gt;
•   Bikes not Bombs: &lt;a href=&quot;http://bikesnotbombs.org/&quot; title=&quot;http://bikesnotbombs.org/&quot;&gt;http://bikesnotbombs.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Boulder, CO has a community bicycle webpage with a comprehensive list of local bike shops&lt;br /&gt;
•   walk to work&lt;br /&gt;
•   ask about reduced rates at local YMCA&lt;br /&gt;
•   Peoples’ acupuncture&lt;br /&gt;
•   Aesthetician/Beauty school students offer reduced rates for massages, haircuts, facials, etc.&lt;br /&gt;
•   Dental schools students similarly offer reduced rates for services (sign up early)&lt;br /&gt;
•   Health food stores have on-site doctors who do consultations&lt;br /&gt;
•   P90X workout plan (share workout)&lt;br /&gt;
•   cheap prescription eyewear: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zennioptical.com/home.php&quot; title=&quot;http://www.zennioptical.com/home.php&quot;&gt;http://www.zennioptical.com/home.php&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Planned Parenthood&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Living Space&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•   Share internet&lt;br /&gt;
•   Wireless extender (pigtail)&lt;br /&gt;
•   Free and cheap stuff&lt;br /&gt;
•      &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.freecycle.org/&quot; title=&quot;http://www.freecycle.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.freecycle.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   free sections on local Craigslist page&lt;br /&gt;
•   community drives&lt;br /&gt;
•   Time exchange&lt;br /&gt;
•   Community bulletin boards&lt;br /&gt;
•   Bulk trash nights&lt;br /&gt;
•   Thrift stores&lt;br /&gt;
•   Cinderblocks and wood furniture&lt;br /&gt;
•   Electric blanket&lt;br /&gt;
•   Heating co-op&lt;br /&gt;
•   Shrink-wrap windows&lt;br /&gt;
•   Heating bill budget plan&lt;br /&gt;
•   St. Vincent de Paul emergency aid for utilities&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Food&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•   Garden, community garden&lt;br /&gt;
•   Volunteer for food (at farm, etc.)&lt;br /&gt;
•   Food not Bombs: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.foodnotbombs.net/&quot; title=&quot;http://www.foodnotbombs.net/&quot;&gt;http://www.foodnotbombs.net/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Farmers’ markets will often double food stamps&lt;br /&gt;
•   Cheap prices at farmers’ markets right before closing&lt;br /&gt;
•   Volunteer at co-op&lt;br /&gt;
•   Canning: Ball Blue Book of Canning&lt;br /&gt;
•   Befriend Starbucks employees&lt;br /&gt;
•   Health food stores on delivery day&lt;br /&gt;
•   Dumpster diving&lt;br /&gt;
•   Federal share program&lt;br /&gt;
•   Food banks (staff will also know other places to get cheap food)&lt;br /&gt;
•   Project Bread: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.projectbread.org&quot; title=&quot;http://www.projectbread.org&quot;&gt;http://www.projectbread.org&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Buy with me: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.buywithme.com/&quot; title=&quot;http://www.buywithme.com/&quot;&gt;http://www.buywithme.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Groupon: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.groupon.com/&quot; title=&quot;http://www.groupon.com/&quot;&gt;http://www.groupon.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Cheapeats&lt;br /&gt;
•   Potlucks&lt;br /&gt;
•   Canned foods&lt;br /&gt;
•   Fishing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Entertainment&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•   Find listservs for free stuff to do&lt;br /&gt;
•   Young nonprofits professional: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ynpn.org/s/936/start.aspx&quot; title=&quot;http://www.ynpn.org/s/936/start.aspx&quot;&gt;http://www.ynpn.org/s/936/start.aspx&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   VISTA Campus&lt;br /&gt;
•   Couchsurfing: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.couchsurfing.org/&quot; title=&quot;http://www.couchsurfing.org/&quot;&gt;http://www.couchsurfing.org/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Four Square: &lt;a href=&quot;http://foursquare.com/&quot; title=&quot;http://foursquare.com/&quot;&gt;http://foursquare.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Meetup: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.meetup.com/&quot; title=&quot;http://www.meetup.com/&quot;&gt;http://www.meetup.com/&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br /&gt;
•   Skill share networks&lt;br /&gt;
•   Art Walk (free museum nights/ open studio nights)&lt;br /&gt;
•   University lectures&lt;br /&gt;
•   Public library&lt;br /&gt;
•   Reading groups/ book clubs&lt;br /&gt;
•   Public access/ community radio&lt;br /&gt;
•   Volunteer&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Budget Ideas&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;•   &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mint.com/&quot;&gt;Mint&lt;/a&gt; (free through Quicken)&lt;br /&gt;
•   Former VISTA has established doc template that VISTAS can access to create budget-related strategies&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
